nostrud exerci tation ullamcorper suscipit lobortis nis ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat. Duis autem vel eum iriure dolor in hendrerit in vulputate velit esse molestie consequat, vel illum dolore eu feugiat nulla facilisis at vero eros et accumsan et iusto odio dignissim. Qui blandit praesent luptatum zzril delenit augue duis dolore te feugait nulla\", \"donate_title\": \"Help people in need\", \"donate_text\": \"START DONATING TODAY, MAKE THE DIFFERENCE\", \"donate_button\": \"\"}, \"es\": {\"h1_title\": \"Una Nueva Etapa en Venezuela con COVID-19\", \"posted_by\": \"\", \"h3_1\": \"\", \"paragraph_1\": \"\", \"paragraph_2\": \"\", \"h3_2\": \"\", \"paragraph_3\": \"\", \"donate_title\": \"\", \"donate_text\": \"\", \"donate_button\": \"\"}}', '{\"en\": \"<h1>A New Era In Venezuela with COVID-19</h1><br>\\r\\n<p>If you think your life has changed in America and the UK since the COVID-19 pandemic, you should see what’s happening in Venezuela.</p>\\r\\n<p>As I am sure you know, SAI has a rich history of delivering nutritious meals to patients in local Venezuelan hospitals. We’ve always been welcome, but due to the virus, all that has come to a full STOP.</p>\\r\\n<p>New Rules About COVID-19 in Venezeulan Hospitals</p>\\r\\n<p>With the failing medical system being pushed to the breaking point, the government has decided not to allow any humanitarian aid to hospital patients. This new rule is enacted by the government to prevent the spread of Covid-19.</p>\\r\\n<p>Clinic Opening</p>\\r\\n<p>As you may know from our previous reports, we’ve converted the first floor of our SAI headquarters in Venezuela to a medical clinic.</p>\\r\\n<p>This medical clinic is providing primary medical care to children and orphans to include medical examinations, testing and medications. We are reallocating our resources from the hospitals to the clinic to help children in need of medical care. The clinic is fully operational with two medical doctors and one full time receptionist.</p>\\r\\n\", \"es\": \"<h1>Una Nueva Etapa en Venezuela con COVID-19</h1>\\r\\n<p>Por Steven Malca - Presidente</p>\\r\\n<p>Si cree que la vida ha cambiado en Estados Unidos o el Reino Unido desde la pandemia de COVID-19, usted debería ver lo que está sucediendo en Venezuela.Estamos seguro de que usted conoce la rica historia de SAI en la entrega de comidas nutritivas a pacientes de hospitales locales venezolanos. Y aunque siempre hemos sido bienvenidos, todo eso se detuvo por completo debido al Virus.</p>\\r\\n<p>Nuevas reglas sobre COVID-19 en hospitales venezolanos</p>\\r\\n<p>A pesar de que el fallido sistema médico en Venezuela ha llegado a su limite, el gobierno ha decidido no permitir ninguna ayuda humanitaria a los pacientes de los hospitales. Según el gobierno, esta nueva regla es promulgada para evitar la propagación de Covid-19.</p>\\r\\n<p>de la Clínica</p>\\r\\n<p>Como sabrá por nuestros informes anteriores, hemos convertido el primer piso de nuestra sede de SAI en una clínica médica totalmente gratuita.</p>\\r\\n<p>Esta clínica médica brinda atención médica primaria a niños y huérfanos incluyendo exámenes médicos, pruebas y medicamentos. Estamos reasignando los recursos que brindamos a los hospitales a nuestra clínica para ayudar a los niños que necesitan atención médica con urgencia. La clínica está en pleno funcionamiento con dos médicos y una recepcionista de tiempo completo.</p>\\r\\n\"}', '{\"en\": {\"seo_title\": \"SAI Adapts to COVID-19: Shifting from Hospital Aid to Children’s Clinic in Venezuela\", \"seo_description\": \"Venezuela’s hospitals banned humanitarian aid over COVID-19. SAI now runs a children’s clinic with doctors & free care. Support our mission today\", \"keywords\": \"Venezuela COVID-19 crisis, SAI medical clinic Venezuela, humanitarian aid Venezuela, children’s healthcare Venezuela, orphan medical care, Venezuela hospital restrictions, pandemic response Venezuela, nonprofit healthcare Venezuela, donate for Venezuelan children, medical aid crisis\", \"og_title\": \"SAI Adapts to COVID-19: Shifting from Hospital Aid to Children’s Clinic in Venezuela\", \"og_description\": \"Venezuela’s hospitals banned humanitarian aid over COVID-19. SAI now runs a children’s clinic with doctors & free care. Support our mission today\"}, \"es\": {\"seo_title\": \"Una Nueva Etapa en Venezuela con COVID-19\", \"seo_description\": \"Una Nueva Etapa en Venezuela con COVID-19\", \"keywords\": null, \"og_title\": \"Una Nueva Etapa en Venezuela con COVID-19\", \"og_description\": \"Una Nueva Etapa en Venezuela con COVID-19\"}}', 'published', 0, '2025-08-13 23:32:43', 1, 1, NULL, '2025-08-13 23:32:43');
