 animals.Exciting news awaits as we introduce a new project: the construction of a gazebo at our sanctuary. This addition is designed to improve the quality of life for our friendly canine residents by offering them a cozy and sheltered area to relax and play. Stay tuned for updates on this thrilling project as we remain committed to the happiness and welfare of our furry companions.Thank you for your ongoing support. Consider becoming a monthly donor and let\'s collaborate towards a brighter future for all dogs in Venezuela.</p>\\r\\n<p><strong>During the first quarter of the year (January to March), SAI\'s animal rescue program distributed a total of (109 sacks) of food to feed the dogs at the SAI-A&G Sanctuary. Furthermore, more than 95 sacks of dog food were provided to our partner shelters.We are delighted to announce that our program has supplied,  (95 sacks) of dog food to our cherished partner shelters, making a total of  given ensuring that more dogs receive the necessary nourishment. This continuous initiative highlights our dedication to supporting the well-being of all shelter animals.Exciting news awaits as we introduce a new project: the construction of a gazebo at our sanctuary. This addition is designed to improve the quality of life for our friendly canine residents by offering them a cozy and sheltered area to relax and play. Stay tuned for updates on this thrilling project as we remain committed to the happiness and welfare of our furry companions.Thank you for your ongoing support. Consider becoming a monthly donor and let\'s collaborate towards a brighter future for all dogs in Venezuela.</strong></p>\\r\\n\", \"es\": \"<h1>SAI Venezuela está salvando vidas, un perro a la vez: comida y refugio para mascotas abandonadas en Venezuela</h1>\\r\\n<p>Durante el primer trimestre del año (de enero a marzo), el programa de rescate de animales de SAI distribuyó un total de 6.002 libras (109 sacos) de comida para alimentar a los perros del Santuario SAI-A&